svg.desc: Using two maps of Germany, the chart shows the availability of internet access of at least 50 Mbit/s for the years 2010 and 2016. Compared to 2010, the number of households with high-speed internet access has increased. But there are still many counties in rural regions where only a small proportion of the population had high-speed internet access. Regional focal points for low coverage are Bavaria, Saxony, Saxony-Anhalt and Thuringia.

div.div: Share of households with 50 Mbit/s internet access
